==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scandent
<hw>Scan"dent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>scandens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>scandere</ets> to
climb.]</ety> <def>Climbing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Scandent plants may climb either by twining, as the hop,
or by twisted leafstalks, as the clematis, or by tendrils, as the
passion flower, or by rootlets, as the ivy.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scandia</ent>⟦br⟧
